    (104,'Assira Jadeed Society (Historic, 1940''s)','2809 Salina Dearborn, MI','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL','1940''s','NULL','NULL','1950','NULL','The New Generation Society is listed in Dearborn City Directories at this address in the 1940''s.  It is not known if this society was religious in orientation, but the name resembles that of the Islamic association that established the first mosque in Cedar Rapids in teh 1930''s.','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL'),
